   Iran Kills 14 Bandits 

   Fourteen armed bandits were killed in Iran's southern province of
   Kerman in the past three months, according to a report here today.

   Iran's official news agency IRNA said that law enforcement forces
   launched 25 armed operations against armed bandits and smugglers and
   seized some 3,193 kilograms of narcotics.

   The report added that 127 pieces of weapons of different types, a large
   amount of ammunition, 42 vehicles and motorcycles were also confiscated
   from the smugglers and bandits.

   During the operations, 740 smugglers and 321 addicts were arrested for
   selling and distributing narcotics.

   Two notorious bandits, Kamandu Shah Bakhsh and Feiz Mohammad Shah
   Bakhsh, were killed by the law enforcement forces of Kerman.
